Zones:
3-10


Sun Exposure:
Full sun (6+ hours daily)


Planting:
Broccoli can be planted either in the early spring or in the mid-summer.
Plant the seeds 1/2 inch deep and 3 inches apart.


Care:
Water 1-1.5 inches per week.
Use a low-nitrogen fertilizer 3 weeks after planting.


Diseases:
Aphids
Nitrogen deficiency


Harvest:
To harvest cut the heads and around 6 inches of stalk from the plant.


Storage:
Store in the refrigerator for up to 5 days, or frozen for up to a year.


Varieties:



Fun Facts:
Broccoli originally comes from Italy.

